==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Peaceable
<hw>Peace"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>peisible</ets>, F. <ets>paisible</ets>.]</ety> <def>Begin in or at
peace; tranquil; quiet; free from, or not disposed to, war, disorder, or
excitement; not quarrelsome.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Peace"a*ble*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>Peace"a*bly</wf>, adv.</wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Peaceful; pacific; tranquil; quiet; mild;
undisturbed; serene; still.</syn> -- <usage><er>Peaceable</er>,
<er>Peaceful</er>. <xex>Peaceable</xex> describes the state of an
individual, nation, etc., in reference to external hostility, attack,
etc.; <xex>peaceful</xex>, in respect to internal disturbance. The
former denotes ⟦ldquo⟧in the spirit of peace;⟦rdquo⟧ latter; ⟦ldquo⟧in
the possession or enjoyment of peace.⟦rdquo⟧ A <xex>peaceable</xex>
adjustment of difficulties; a <xex>peaceful</xex> life,
scene.</usage>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peacebreaker</ent>⟦br⟧
